00:25:07.560 --> 00:25:10.250
So my biggest concern
in American politics

00:25:10.250 --> 00:25:13.640
is the interaction
between party polarization

00:25:13.640 --> 00:25:20.290
and a disaggregated checks
and balance-oriented system.

00:25:20.290 --> 00:25:21.850
So when I think
about what you need

00:25:21.850 --> 00:25:24.650
to change in American
politics, basically my argument

00:25:24.650 --> 00:25:28.950
is party polarization is
not a transient phenomenon.

00:25:28.950 --> 00:25:33.210
It is the equilibrium of
a multiparty democracy.

00:25:33.210 --> 00:25:38.120
And what is seen as
the sort of golden age

00:25:38.120 --> 00:25:40.380
of American politics,
sort of mid-20th century

00:25:40.380 --> 00:25:43.030
period in which the parties were
non-polarized, where you could

00:25:43.030 --> 00:25:44.930
have a hardcore
conservative like Strom

00:25:44.930 --> 00:25:47.370
Thurmond, the Democratic
Party, and a hardcore liberal

00:25:47.370 --> 00:25:51.670
like, hey, George Romney
in the Republican Party,

00:25:51.670 --> 00:25:52.730
that is the aberration.

00:25:52.730 --> 00:25:54.550
That is the thing that
didn't make sense.

00:25:54.550 --> 00:25:56.466
The problem is we have
a political system that

00:25:56.466 --> 00:25:58.510
does not work with polarization.

00:25:58.510 --> 00:25:59.920
The aberration was about race.

00:25:59.920 --> 00:26:02.780
When race receded from the
front of American politics,

00:26:02.780 --> 00:26:05.090
the aberration began
to resolve itself.

00:26:05.090 --> 00:26:07.540
And now we are in
a position where

00:26:07.540 --> 00:26:09.960
we have essentially
parliamentary style

00:26:09.960 --> 00:26:12.600
parties without
parliamentary style rules.

00:26:12.600 --> 00:26:15.400
So if I were going to start
amending the Constitution,

00:26:15.400 --> 00:26:18.380
and I want to be very clear
that if left to my own devices,

00:26:18.380 --> 00:26:19.060
I would not.

00:26:19.060 --> 00:26:20.768
Because I think
constitutional amendments

00:26:20.768 --> 00:26:22.050
are very tough things.

00:26:22.050 --> 00:26:24.990
But within the context
of the question,

00:26:24.990 --> 00:26:26.870
I would be looking
to move America

00:26:26.870 --> 00:26:30.140
closer to a parliamentary
style political system,

00:26:30.140 --> 00:26:33.990
where in the president
and the majority

00:26:33.990 --> 00:26:36.960
and Congress are
matched in a clearer way

00:26:36.960 --> 00:26:38.770
than is currently the case.

00:26:38.770 --> 00:26:43.240
It is a troubling fact, if
think about it long enough,

00:26:43.240 --> 00:26:47.410
that America is the only
constitutional presidential

00:26:47.410 --> 00:26:51.780
democracy of its kind to last
for an extremely long time.

00:26:51.780 --> 00:26:55.360
Virtually every other
system constructed like ours

00:26:55.360 --> 00:26:57.270
has collapsed for a
very simple reason.

00:26:57.270 --> 00:26:59.820
That there is no
constitutional way

00:26:59.820 --> 00:27:02.980
to resolve disputes between
the executive, which

00:27:02.980 --> 00:27:05.690
has democratic legitimacy,
and the legislature, which

00:27:05.690 --> 00:27:07.700
also has democratic legitimacy.

00:27:07.700 --> 00:27:10.140
So when you get into something
like congressional Republic

00:27:10.140 --> 00:27:11.890
and say they won't
raise the debt ceiling,

00:27:11.890 --> 00:27:14.280
and Barack Obama says you
gotta raise the debt ceiling,

00:27:14.280 --> 00:27:16.865
we don't actually have an
answer to that, except for well,

00:27:16.865 --> 00:27:18.800
we better come up with one.

00:27:18.800 --> 00:27:23.130
Now, maybe we always will,
but I'm not confident in that.

00:27:23.130 --> 00:27:26.860
So I would be looking to move
us toward something where there

00:27:26.860 --> 00:27:28.740
are clearer lines
of accountability

00:27:28.740 --> 00:27:33.310
and less possibility of
catastrophic breakdown.

00:27:33.310 --> 00:27:35.030
It's, by the way, a
very notable thing

00:27:35.030 --> 00:27:38.809
that we have helped a
number of other countries

00:27:38.809 --> 00:27:40.100
develop their political system.

00:27:40.100 --> 00:27:42.550
You think of the countries we
occupied after World War II,

00:27:42.550 --> 00:27:46.472
like Japan, we have not
pushed them towards ours.

00:27:46.472 --> 00:27:48.430
And the reason is is
actually pretty well known

00:27:48.430 --> 00:27:50.880
in the literature that this
kind of system is unstable.

00:27:50.880 --> 00:27:53.950
It's worked in America
because we've had-- one,

00:27:53.950 --> 00:27:55.540
we're just fucking awesome.

00:27:55.540 --> 00:27:58.710
But two, we've
had, traditionally,

00:27:58.710 --> 00:27:59.605
very diffuse parties.

00:27:59.605 --> 00:28:01.490
It's really unusual.

00:28:01.490 --> 00:28:06.260
But I think the specific unique
qualities of our democracy

00:28:06.260 --> 00:28:08.840
and our party system that
have allowed it to work

00:28:08.840 --> 00:28:10.860
are slowly vanishing,
and I think

00:28:10.860 --> 00:28:14.280
it's putting us in a
position that lends itself

00:28:14.280 --> 00:28:17.120
to very dangerous crises.

